# TypeScript Only

## Always use TypeScript, never JavaScript

This project is TypeScript-only. All code files must use TypeScript.

## File Extensions

### ✅ Correct
- `.ts` for TypeScript files
- `.tsx` for React components with JSX
- `.astro` for Astro components (TypeScript in frontmatter)

### ❌ Never Use
- `.js` files
- `.jsx` files
- `.mjs` files
- `.cjs` files

## Examples

### ✅ Correct
```typescript
// utils/format.ts
export function formatDate(date: Date): string {
  return date.toLocaleDateString()
}

// components/Button.tsx
interface ButtonProps {
  label: string
  onClick: () => void
}

export function Button({ label, onClick }: ButtonProps) {
  return <button onClick={onClick}>{label}</button>
}
```

### ❌ Incorrect
```javascript
// utils/format.js
export function formatDate(date) {
  return date.toLocaleDateString()
}

// components/Button.jsx
export function Button({ label, onClick }) {
  return <button onClick={onClick}>{label}</button>
}
```

## Type Safety

- Define types for all function parameters and return values
- Use interfaces or types for component props
- Leverage TypeScript's type inference where appropriate
- Run `npm run typecheck` to verify type correctness